    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>There is a menu entry you have discovered for yourself that toggles the skipping of all breakpoints. There is also an icon for this in the \"Breakpoints\" View, and there may be a hot-key defined as well, all of which you may have triggered by accident.</p>\n\n<p>Take a look at the <strong>Run -> Skip All Breakpoints</strong>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 90923,
      "reputation" : 78124,
      "user_id" : 249991,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 85,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d294689e27dc65262f99563079112af9?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "UMAR-MOBITSOLUTIONS",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/249991/umar-mobitsolutions"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1388315428,
    "creation_date" : 1388315428,
    "answer_id" : 20824530,
    "question_id" : 7992134,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>1) Run => Skip all breakpoints.\n2) Run => remove all break points.</p>\n\n<p>and then your debugger wont show cross sign and will keep debugging your app.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
